15.  The service of agent by any of the following person:
(a) insurance agent as defined under the Financial Services Act 2013 [Act 758];
(b) estate agent registered under the Valuers, Appraisers, Estate Agents and
Property Managers Act 1981 [Act 242];
(c) money services business agent appointed under the Money Services
Business Act 2011 [Act 731];
(d) mercantile agent as defined under the Sales of Goods Act 1957 [Act 382];
(e) self-employment social security agent appointed under this Act; or
(f) agent in collecting and distributing of zakat appointed by the authorized
person.

16.  The service of professional, scientific and technical by any of the following
person:
(a) advocates and solicitors registered under the Legal Profession Act 1976
[Act 166], the Advocates Ordinance Sabah 1953 (Sabah Cap. 2) or the
Advocates Ordinance Sarawak 1953 (Sarawak Cap. 110);
(b) accountant registered under the Accountants Act 1967 [Act 94] and includes
auditor and tax consultant;
(c) architect registered under the Architects Act 1967 [Act 117];
(d) engineer registered under the Registration of Engineers Act 1967 [Act 138];
(e) research and development which carry out for the purposes of systematic,
investigative and experimental study that involves novelty or technical risk
carried out in the field of science or technology with the object of acquiring
new knowledge or using the results of the study for the production or
improvement of materials, devices, products, produce, or processes, and
includes—
(i) quality control or routine testing of materials, devices or products;
(ii) research in the social sciences or the humanities;
Self-Employment Social Security                                 65
(iii) routine data collection;
(iv) efficiency surveys or management studies;
(v) market research or sales promotion;
(vi) routine modifications or changes to materials, devices, products,
processes or production methods; or
(vii) cosmetic modifications or stylistic changes to materials, devices,
products, processes or production methods;
(f) inventor who has an invention which is patented under the Patents Act 1983
[Act 291];
(g) veterinar doctor which is registered under the Veterinary Surgeons Act 1974
[Act 147];
(h) registered medical practitioner which is registered under the Medical Act
1971 [Act 50];
(i) psychiatrist which has the meaning assigned to it in the Mental Health Act
2001 [Act 615]; or
(j) dental practitioner which is registered under the Dental Act 1971 [Act 51].
